race.comment: EXTINGUISH (11) was much better second-up when chasing gamely into second here last week. Peaking now on the quick back-up and is drawn to get all the favours for Pannell. Can get the job done. SWIFTIE HARRIET (5) got too far back here last week before rattling home to just miss. Expect her to be much closer this time from the better draw and is sure to go close. THE LAST DANCE (3) was an eye-catcher here fresh when resuming three weeks ago. Will drift back again from the wide draw but can cause a late scare. NEW YORK SCANDAL (10) pops over the border and has peaks that measure up. Opperman from a good draw create interest. SAN LUCIDO (8) is more than capable on his day and looks to be back somewhere near his best. Gets in light with the claim and is a genuine each-way hope.
